<h2 style="padding-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(45, 91, 91);">About Me</h2><p style="margin: 5px 0px 20px; line-height: 20px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(87, 87, 87); font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">I'm a Professor at the Department of Computer Science, City University of Hong Kong. I recieved my PhD from Uppsala University, Sweden. Before joining CityU, I worked in The Hong Kong Polytechnic University and Northeastern University, China. My research interests include real-time systems, embedded systems, cyber-physical systems and internet-of-things. Apart form doing theoretical research, I'm also involved in some projects building cool systems, together with my industry parteners.

<h2 style="padding-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(45, 91, 91);">News</h2>
    <ul style="margin-top: 0.5em; font-size: 0.9em; list-style-type: circle;">


 <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Outstanding Paper Award of RTSS 2025. </span>
Our Paper "WCDFP Analysis for Real-Time Tasks with Stochastic Release Patterns using Chernoff Bound" received the Outstanding Paper Award of RTSS 2025
(IEEE Real-Time Systems Symposium).</li>



 <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Best Paper Award of CODES+ISSS 2025. </span>
Our Paper "Re-thinking Memory-Bound Limitations in CGRAs" received the Best Paper Award of CODES+IEEE 2025
(International Conference on Hardware/Software Codesign and System Synthesis).</li>



 <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Outstanding Paper Award of RTAS 2025. </span>
Our Paper "Jointly Ensuring Timing Disparity and End-to-End Latency Constraints in Hybrid DAGs" recieved the Outstanding Paper Award of RTAS 2025
(IEEE Real-Time and Embedded Technology and Applications Symposium).</li>





  <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the General Co-Chair of MEMOCODE 2025 <a href="https://memocode2025.github.io/"> (check details here)</a></span>.</span> 
MEMOCODE's objective is to emphasize the importance of models and methodologies in correct system design and development.
MEMOCODE'25 is a part of ESWEEK 2025, which will take place in Taipei, Taiwan during Sep 28 - Oct 3 2025.


  <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the General Co-Chair of SETTA 2024 <a href="https://setta2024.cs.cityu.edu.hk/"> (check details here)</a></span>.</span> 
The purpose of the SETTA is to bring international researchers to exchange research results and ideas with the Chinese computer science and software engineering community. We hope to develop understanding of the research of different groups so as to encourage closer and interest-driven research collaborations. 
SETTA 2024 will be held in Hong Kong, Nov 26-28, 2024.



  <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Best Paper Award of RTSS 2023. </span>Our Paper "SEAM: An Optimal Message Synchronizer in ROS with Well-Bounded Time Disparity." wins the Best Paper Award of RTSS 2023 (IEEE Real-Time Systems Symposium), the flagship conference in the field of real-time systems.</li>




  <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Local Arrangement Chair of CPS-IoT Week 2024 <a href="https://cps-iot-week2024.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/"> (check details here)</a></span>.</span> 
CPS-IoT Week is the premier event on Cyber-Physical Systems and the Internet-of-Things. It brings together five top conferences, HSCC, ICCPS, IoTDI, IPSN, and RTAS, multiple workshops, tutorials, and competitions.
CPS-IoT Week 2024 will be held in Hong Kong, May 13-16, 2024.





     <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Design and Application Track Chair of RTSS 2023 <a href="http://2023.rtss.org/"> (check details here)</a></span>.</span> 
Please consider submitting your fine work. The IEEE Real-Time Systems Symposium (RTSS) is the premier conference in the field of real-time systems. The 44th IEEE RTSS is to be held in Taipei from Dec. 5 to 8, 2023.




     <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Program Co-Chair of RTCSA 2023 <a href="https://rtcsa2023.github.io/"> (check details here)</a></span>.</span> 
