in TOKI MESSE, Niigata, Japan.



        <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Outstanding Paper Award of RTSS 2022. </span>Our Paper "Bounding the Response Time of DAG Tasks Using Long Paths" wins the Outstanding Paper Award of RTSS 2022 (43th IEEE Real-Time Systems Symposium), the flagship conference in the field of real-time systems.</li>


     <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Keynote Talk at MEMOCODE 2022 <a href="https://memocode2022.github.io/program.html"> (check details here)</a>.</span> 
I gave a keynote talk titled "Towards a Theoretical Foundation for Real-Time Robotic Operating System (ROS)" in 20th ACM-IEEE International Conference on Formal Methods and Models for System Design (MEMOCODE 2022).</li>


      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Selection Committee Chair of SIGBED-SIGSOFT Frank Anger Memorial Award 2022 <a href="https://sigbed.org/2022/09/19/frank-anger-memorial-award-2022/"> (check details here)</a>.</span> The Frank Anger Memorial Award is a student award in the name of the late Dr. Frank Anger that promotes cross-disciplinary research between embedded systems and software engineering. Funding for the award is provided by ACM SIGBED.</li>

     <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the General Co-Chair of ISORC 2023 <a href="https://isorc.github.io/2023/"> (check details here)</a>.</span> Please consider submitting your fine work. 
The 26th IEEE International symposium on Real-Time Distributed Computing is to be held from May 23 to 25 in Nashville, Tennessee, USA. 






<li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the General Chair of RTAS 2022 <a href="http://2022.rtas.org/"> (check details here)</a>.</span> Please consider to submit your fine work. RTAS (IEEE Real-Time and Embedded Technology and Applications Symposium) is a flagship conference in the field of real-time and embedded computing systems. </li>

      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Program Co-Chair of ISORC 2022 <a href="https://isorc2022.github.io/"> (check details here)</a>.</span> Please consider to submit your fine work. 
ISORC (IEEE Symposium on Real-Time Distributed Computing) addresses research into the application of real-time distributed technology, with an emphasis on object-, component- and service-oriented systems and solutions.</li>

      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Selection Committee Chair of SIGBED-SIGSOFT Frank Anger Memorial Award 2021 <a href="https://sigbed.org/2021/07/11/frank-anger-memorial-award-2021/"> (check details here)</a>.</span> The Frank Anger Memorial Award is a student award in the name of the late Dr. Frank Anger that promotes cross-disciplinary research between embedded systems and software engineering. Funding for the award is provided by ACM SIGBED.</li>

      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Industry Chair of RTSS 2021 <a href="http://2021.rtss.org/industry-session/"> (check details here)</a>.</span> RTSS (IEEE Real-Time Systems Symposium) is a flagship conference in the field of real-time and embedded computing systems. The purpose of RTSS 2021 Industry Session is to initiate and strengthen the collaborations between industry and academia in real-time systems research.</li>




   <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Best Paper Award of EMSOFT 2020. </span>Our Paper "Efficient Feasibility Analysis for Graph-based Real-Time Task Systems" wins the Best Paper Award of EMSOFT 2020 (International Conference on Embedded Software), a top conference in the field of embedded computing systems and software.</li>


      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the PC Chair of RTAS 2021.</span> Please consider to submit your fine work. RTAS (IEEE Real-Time and Embedded Technology and Applications Symposium) is a flagship conference in the field of real-time and embedded computing systems. </li>

      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Deputy Track Chair of RTSS 2020 Track 2.</span> RTSS (IEEE Real-Time Systems Symposium) is a flagship conference in the field of real-time and embedded computing systems. </li>

      <li> <span style="color:  rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">2020 ACM SIGBED Early Career Researcher Award.</span> ACM SIGBED is a focal point within the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM) for all aspects of embedded computing systems and cyber-physical systems, including both software and hardware. ACM SIGBED in 2017 established the Early Career Researcher Award to recognize contributions by junior researchers in the area of embedded, real-time, and cyber-physical systems.</li>




      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the Track Co-Chair of ICPADS 2020, Architecture Track.</span> Please consider to submit your fine work. ICPADS (IEEE International Conference on Parallel and Distributed Systems) is a major international forum for scientists and engineers to exchange and share new ideas and their latest research results regarding systems that are inherently parallel and/or distributed. </li>


      <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Outstanding Paper Award of RTSS 2019. </span>Our Paper "Mixed-Criticality Multicore Scheduling of Real-Time Gang Task Systems" wins the Outstanding Paper Award and Best Student Paper Award of RTSS 2019 (IEEE Real-Time Systems Symposium), a flagship conference in the field of real-time and embedded computing theory and systems.</li>

      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve on the TCRTS Executive Committee.</span> TCRTS (IEEE Technical Committee on Real-Time Systems)  promotes and facilitates the exchange of research results and development in the areas of real-time systems, including applications, databases, distributed and parallel systems, formal methods and timing analysis, networks, operating systems and middleware, programming languages, scheduling and resource management, security, and verification and validation. </li>



      <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Best Paper Award of ISORC 2019. </span>Our Paper "Improving Multiprocessor Real-Time Systems with Bursty Inputs under Global EDF using Shapers" wins the Best Paper Award of ISORC 2019 (IEEE International Symposium on Real-Time Distributed Computing).</li>


      <li> <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Serve as the PC Chair of SETTA 2019.</span> Please consider to submit your fine work. SETTA (Symposium on Dependable Software Engineering) will take place in Shanghai, China, Nov. 28-29, 2019.</li>

      <li>  <span style="color: rgb(0, 100, 150); font-weight: bold;">Best Paper Award of e-Energy 2018. </span>Our Paper "Data Driven Chiller Sequencing for Reducing HVAC Electricity Consumption in Commercial Buildings" wins the Best Paper Award of e-Energy 2018 (International Conference on Future Energy Systems).</li>

  </ul>



